      <description>Ted Savoie was born in 1943 in Galliano, Louisiana, to a family with
            Acadian heritage (descendants of Fran{cedil}cois Savoie). He spent his childhood living
            with his immediate family and maternal grandfather, who was in the oyster business and a
            community leader. Savoie's father was originally a farmer from Larose, but entered the
            oyster business and then the tugboat business, which Savoie eventually took over. Savoie
            is active in church and civic activities, and the father of four children and many
            grandchildren.</description>
