   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/bayoulafourche/Savoie_Ted_T3935.pdf">Savoie discusses his grandfather's influence on his early years. He explains the
            importance of the Catholic Church in his daily life, growing up, and for his children
            and their families. He talks about the role of music and dance halls in his youth, and
            how he helped to bring musicians to the bayou. Savoie discusses the importance of
            volunteering in the community, including his own role in the development of the Oyster
            Festival. Savoie discusses the various homes he has lived in, and the changing
            demographics of Bayou Lafourche, in terms of religion and race.</abstract>
